721645f-a.title: Manhattan: Mill Lane - William Street (South)
721645f-a.text:
Mill Lane, north from South William, to and including Stone Streets.
Also shown is Nos. 60-62 Stone Street, adjoining the S.E. corner of Hanover
Square.
July 6, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
721645f-a.folder: Mill Lane & William Street (South), Manhattan, NY

723356f-c.title: Manhattan: South William Street - Mill Lane
723356f-c.text:
(1)
South William Street, east from but not including Mill Lane, to and
including Beaver Street (where 10--story building is seen being prepared
for demolition). Also shown is William Street (left) north from Beaver
to Wall Streets. The building at the apex is that of the Farmers Loan
and Trust Co., at the N.E. corner of William and Beaver Streets, and is
in process of being razed to make room for a new 59-story skyscraper,
called the City Bank Farmers Truat Building.
July 6, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A part of the same, exposing to view the Beaver Street side of the
Farmers Loan and Trust Co. Building and eliminating William Street.
July 6, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NN2( e t75-d
(3)
The same, at a later date, showing the clearance created by the
demolition of the Farmers Loan and Trust Co. Building (where steam shovels
are workiihg), and across it a part of the National City Bank Building.
In the background are seen (left to right) the Bank of New York and Trust
Co. and the National City Buildings.
August 24, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
N w U18.A
